<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="528" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[344,557,152,176]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Monimiaceae" genus="Hellerenius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="13" pageNumber="528" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobifer">
<emphasis box="[344,557,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">Hellerenius lobifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
turns out to be a much less common species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1110,1285,151,176]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
than the two other species described below, namely 
<taxonomicName box="[612,752,188,212]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Monimiaceae" genus="Hellerenius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="13" pageNumber="528" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumipes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[612,632,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[651,752,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">plumipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[764,856,189,212]" pageId="13" pageNumber="528" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[920,1037,188,212]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Monimiaceae" genus="Hellerenius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="13" pageNumber="528" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tibialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[920,940,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[959,1037,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1049,1140,189,212]" pageId="13" pageNumber="528" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
It also seems to express different phenology being mostly collected between January and October, while both 
<taxonomicName box="[1128,1265,224,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Monimiaceae" genus="Hellerenius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="13" pageNumber="528" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumipes">
<emphasis box="[1128,1148,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1164,1265,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">plumipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1322,1435,224,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Monimiaceae" genus="Hellerenius" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="13" pageNumber="528" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tibialis">
<emphasis box="[1322,1342,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1358,1435,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="528">tibialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were predominantly found in November–February.
</paragraph>
